      "span_text": "Another response to shock is an increase in self-administration of opiates in rats. Lever pressing for access to a fentanyl solution sped up after shock, and when water or quinine (which has a similar taste to fentanyl) was substituted for the agonist, extinction occurred [CITATION_2] , indicating that opiate actions were involved in the change, with stress-released endogenous opiates potentiating the exogenous one."
